                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="alleyn_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1566-1626) an English actor, famous for his performances in plays by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/christopher-marlowe#christopher_marlowe_topg_1" title="Marlowe definition"><span class="ndv">Marlowe</span></a>, while his great <span class="ndv" tofix="" href="rival_subentryg_1:rival_topg_4">rival</span> Richard Burbage (c. 1567-1619) acted in Shakespeare's plays. He owned the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-rose-theatre#the_rose_theatre_topg_1" title="Rose Theatre definition"><span class="ndv">Rose Theatre</span></a>, and provided the money to establish <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/dulwich-college" title="Dulwich College definition"><span class="ndv">Dulwich College</span></a>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
